Former President Olusegun Obasanjo has lauded the performance of Governor Aminu Tambuwal of Sokoto state, saying he has done well in office. NAN reports that the elder statesman spoke on Sunday when he laid the foundation stone for the N3.4 billion nine-span flyover in Sokoto, Obasanjo said despite the economy, security challenges and COVID-19, Tambuwal has been “making things go on”. The ex-Head of State called his host “a performing governor within the northwest especially in handling issues of insecurity”. Obasanjo stressed that Tambuwal was doing well among his colleagues and for his party. “I pray God gives him strength, wisdom and ability to do more”, he said. Obasanjo added that a summary of assessments indicated that Tambuwal’s achievements “have outspoken his integrity”.